Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author  benchmark-task-prep
    Description Container image for simple compression-benchmark task. \
                Provides Python, pytest and common compressors. \
                Leaves /home/user clean so that the student can create the \
                required artefacts during execution.

%post
    set -e

    # Update package lists and install required tools
    apt-get update -y
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        gzip \
        bzip2 \
        xz-utils \
        time \
        ca-certificates

    # Install pytest for the grader
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Create a writable work directory for the student / CI job
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Clean up to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Ensure user-level Python packages (if any) end up in PATH
    export PATH="/home/user/.local/bin:${PATH}"

%runscript
    # Default entrypoint: just launch an interactive shell
    exec /bin/bash "$@"

%help
    This image supplies:
      • gzip, bzip2, xz compressors
      • GNU time utility for simple benchmarking
      • Python 3 + pytest for automated grading

    The workspace /home/user is empty and writable; the student will
    perform all tasks inside that directory.